            "name": "What does this Base64 to JSON converter do?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "This tool decodes a Base64 string using atob(), then attempts to parse the decoded text as JSON using JSON.parse(). If parsing succeeds, the output is displayed as pretty-printed JSON with 2-space indentation. If the decoded content is not valid JSON, the raw decoded text is shown with a note. All processing runs in your browser — no data is sent to a server."
            }
        }, {
