            "name": "Can I use this tool to decode JWT payloads?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Yes. Paste the middle section of a JWT (between the first and second dot) into the input. JWT tokens use URL-safe Base64 without padding — this tool automatically handles the URL-safe alphabet and adds padding as needed. The decoded payload shows the JWT claims such as sub, iat, exp, and custom fields."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What happens if the decoded content is not valid JSON?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "If the Base64 string decodes to something that is not valid JSON — such as plain text or binary data — the tool displays the raw decoded text with a note explaining that JSON parsing was not possible. You can still copy the raw decoded content."
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
